{
  "stem": "24814.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Wasseralfingen ?] in northern Bavaria, and the news came over the radio that the surrender at Reims.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Donitz, the German admiral had surrendered.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "No underground, no werewolves, no resistance, it's all over.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I walked into the command post where the colonel and three battalion commanders were planning roadblocks and operations, and I said, gentlemen, by the way, the war just ended.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they looked at me and said, oh, yeah, thanks, doc, OK, and went right on planning.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They couldn't stop what they were doing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Finally, that night we celebrated.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But we were up at a city called Dillingen on the Danube where we had gotten the bridge.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We-- they moved-- shuffled us around, a couple days after the surrender.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And a young Captain Levy, Matt [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Levy ?] from New York, [INAUDIBLE], stopped in to have lunch at our officer's mess.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When you travel you stopped in at other officer's mess for lunch, or something.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he told me he was working at Dachau, in the typhus center.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He described the conditions there, and the food problems they were having, and things like that.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I-- I got like I ought to help out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had no more wounded to take care of.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had nothing to do in my official capacity.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had plenty of medical personnel for the kids that got sick or something.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So with the consent of my commanding officer, I took my ambulance and drove through Augsburg and down to Dachau, to the 66th Field Hospital, which was the typhus center.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Introduced myself to the colonel, commanding officer, and he said, fine, major, always glad to have extra hands.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Welcome aboard.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I got sprayed with DDT to kill lice, of course.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
